        DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN 

             SSEETTIIMMEE sets the system time depending on the values in the 
             structure _b_u_f_f_e_r as defined in TTIIMMEE.HH.  These values must 
             be set prior to calling SSEETTIIMMEE or the system time will be 
             set to an unknown state.  

             GGEETTIIMMEE reads the system time and returns the information in 
             the structure _b_u_f_f_e_r.  Reading the structure elements will 
             then yield the desired values.  

             An example to read the time structure might be: 

                  struct sgtbuf timepacket;

                  getime(timepacket);
                  printf("The year is: %d", timepacket.t_year);
                  printf("The day is:  %d", timepacket.t_day);


